parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the driveshaft from the vehicle can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The rear U-joint and connected driveshaft separate from the vehicle
potentially causing loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seals can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on the rear axle and potentially causing loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Fluid leaks from the rear axle
potentially causing premature wear on the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The manual transmission fails
causing shifting mechanism and clutch failure
resulting in no clutch operation while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The clutch fails
resulting in no clutch operation while driving
requiring repeated replacement of the clutch assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Travel and Spongy Brake Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brake pedal travel and spongy brake pedal can lead to extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels too far before the brakes engage
the brakes require excessive pressure to stop the vehicle
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle or differential can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when stopping or slowing down.
symptoms: The rear end of the vehicle collapses or sags
the differential drops or falls
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear axle
difficulty steering or maintaining control
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake cable can cause the rear brakes to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected brake lockup
ABS activation
difficulty stopping the vehicle
unusual noises or vibrations when applying the brakes.
